olive oil
1 packet beef strips
½ packet garlic paste
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 packet roasted peanuts
1 cucumber
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 bag coriander
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 bag Asian Slaw Mix

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat
• Season beef strips and cook in
batches until browned, 1 min
• Return all beef to the pan, then add
garlic paste and cook until fragrant,
1 min
• Remove pan from heat, then add
sweet chilli sauce, tossing to combine

• Microwave rice until steaming,
2-3 mins
• Crush roasted peanuts in their packet
• Add peanuts and rice to a bowl.
Season and stir to combine

• Roughly chop cucumber
• In a bowl, combine cucumber, slaw
mix and ponzu sauce. Season
• Plate up rice, slaw and beef
• Serve with garlic aioli and crispy
shallots. Garnish with torn coriander
to serve